# =============================================================================
#  This repo is a TOOL. The lecture material you point it at is NOT part of it.
#
#  Recordings, transcripts, extracted frames and the finished script are the
#  intellectual property of whoever gave the lecture. They live in `work/` and
#  `videos/`, both ignored wholesale, and they must never be committed here.
#  Keep them in a PRIVATE repo (see README -> "Keeping your content out of git").
#  A pre-commit hook enforces this:  scripts/install-hooks.sh
# =============================================================================
videos/
work/

# Belt and braces. `work/` above already covers these, but if the layout ever
# changes, content must still not become committable by accident.
*.mp4
*.mov
*.m4v
*.mkv
*.mp3
*.wav
*.m4a
